<p class="">I will not give an exact figure, but it is appreciably less than the figure he has mentioned. From the point <span id="1725" class="column-number" data-column-number="1725"></span> of view of an answer to the right hon. and learned Gentleman's speech, that is rather a pity because point after point in his speech, as the Committee will remember, following that assertion, was based on the hypothesis of a dreadfully bad bargain which we had obviously made, because the price which we had given for maize exceeded £30 a ton. The price did not exceed £30 a ton but was very appreciably less, so that that part of the right hon. and learned Gentleman's argument falls to the ground. I need say no more about it.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
